## Mission Control turn completion

Turn-end structured choice is keyed by dispatch **`trustLevel`** — normative detail lives in [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/2_ask-question-instructions.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/2_ask-question-instructions.mdc) § **Checkpoint trust level — binary host contract** and § **Turn completion invariant**:

| Trust | Agent obligation (summary) |
|-------|----------------------------|
| **`checkpoint`** | Gate surfaces (`USER_CHECKPOINT`, external-wait, exceptions) **must** close with **`AskQuestion`** / **`mission_control_present_structured_choice`**. Happy-path protocol steps between gates **Act** without a turn-end modal — **never** prose-only idle when you cannot advance. |
| **`tool_execution`** / **`user_in_full_control`** | Host every-turn structured-choice policy — close with **`AskQuestion`** / MCP structured choice; not prose-only exit. |

Spawned lanes without the AskQuestion tool **must** call **`mission_control_present_structured_choice`** when a gate surface (or non-Checkpoint every-turn policy) requires structured choice. Full wire format: rule **2** § *`mission_control_present_structured_choice` MCP tool contract (binding)*. **Forbidden:** treating this bootstrap summary as license to skip Checkpoint gate modals, or as requiring a modal on every Checkpoint happy-path hop.

---

## No agent gcloud secrets or env-var proposals (binding)

Agents **must not** update gcloud secrets, add environment variables to code, or **propose** new env vars. Env vars require an **explicit same-turn developer instruction** naming the variable. Normative detail: [`60_no-agent-env-secrets.mdc`](60_no-agent-env-secrets.mdc).

## Checkpoint step continuation (binding)

This file is the **sole R&D alwaysApply warm-up bind** — plan-and-deliver routing summary, lane warm-up manifest contract, and on-demand links to numbered R&D rules. It is **not** a mission protocol with executable ship steps. Under **`trustLevel: checkpoint`**, step-continuation UX for worktrees, ship chain, and planning gates lives in invoker skills and numbered R&D rules **10**–**60** (plus Sedea rules via platform bootstrap). **Do not** add literal `USER_CHECKPOINT` markers here for happy-path warm-up, lane-manifest reads, or on-demand rule hops — that would fight skill auto-advance.

| Surface | Designation | Owner |
|---------|-------------|--------|
| Warm-up apply (R&D bootstrap + laneRules + skillWarmUp) | **auto-advance** | Host merge; this file as R&D `bootstrapRules` |
| Lane warm-up manifest / merge-order reads | **auto-advance** | This § *Lane warm-up manifest* |
| On-demand numbered R&D rule loads (`10`–`60`) | **auto-advance** | Lane manifest / skill `Read` — no USER_CHECKPOINT in bootstrap |
| Skill helper interface hop | **auto-advance** | This § *Skill helper interfaces* — execution owned by named skill |
| Turn completion (trust-keyed) | **baseline-governs** (reference) | Sedea rule **2** (Checkpoint binary + non-Checkpoint every-turn); summary table above |
| No idle handoff | **baseline-governs** (reference) | Sedea rules **1**–**2**; Forbidden catalog below |

**Forbidden in this file:** prescribing prose *tell me when* / *come back when* / *I'll wait* / *over to you* / *ask how to proceed* as the primary wait surface; `USER_CHECKPOINT` tokens for happy-path warm-up or on-demand rule hops; duplicating rule-2 AskQuestion option tables or skill gate markers; requiring a modal on every Checkpoint happy-path hop; unkeyed every-turn AskQuestion summaries.

**Related:** Checkpoint step-table template — [`.sedea/centers/sedea/docs/pr-step-table-template.md`](.sedea/centers/sedea/docs/pr-step-table-template.md). Marker syntax — [`.sedea/centers/sedea/docs/user-checkpoint-marker-syntax.md`](.sedea/centers/sedea/docs/user-checkpoint-marker-syntax.md).

